====== short ======
Does not provide insight into the direction of time. Does however, provide
general though uncompelling support for the(/my) view that causation is a second
tier <q>concept</q> tied to our position as agents choosing our next action, and
having no part to play in mature scientific theories in which we are <q>limning
the true and ultimate structure of reality</q>(([[local:zz.texts/quine1960-wordAndObject.pdf]])).
Some further citations supporting this view of causation - nice to know it is at
least a (though not _the_) orthodox position among physicists.

